<taxonomicNameLabel id="0CDE4E671035FFAAD91EF8224E402CAC" box="[571,629,1897,1921]" pageId="16" pageNumber="117" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(62) Head–pelta (female, mac); (63) Head– pelta (female, mic); (64) Antenna, dorsal aspect (female, mic); (65) Antennal segments III–VIII, ventral aspect (female, mac); (66) Antennal segments III–VIII, ventral aspect (female, mic); (67) Basantra–mesopresternum (female, mac); (68) Fore tibia &amp; tarsus (female, mac); (69) Fore tibia &amp; tarsus (male, mac); (70) Fore wing; (71) Tube (female, mac).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="25262F0E1034FFABDBE2FFDC491E2A6C" blockId="17.[151,1437,150,646]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="17EDF31C1034FFABDBE2FFDC4D432B9C" bold="true" box="[199,374,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">Measurements</emphasis>
. Male 
<typeStatus id="FA2291AC1034FFABDAE3FFDC4E132B9C" box="[454,550,151,177]" pageId="17" pageNumber="118">paratype</typeStatus>
(mic.) in microns. Distended body length about 1500. Head length 150, width across cheeks 135. Compound eye dorsal length 48–50. Pronotum length 115, width 190. Fore wing length 150. Tube length 85, width across base 52. Antenna length about 340, segments III–VIII length (width) as follows: 50 (28), 50 (30), 43 (25), 42.5 (22), 41 (20), 28 (12). Postocular setae?45. Pronotal aa 30–35, am 35–36, ml about 40, pa about 40, epim 45–46. S1 setae on tergite IX 75–76, S2 setae on tergite IX 29–31. Anal setae 95–100.
</paragraph>
